In the physical sense, pouring (usually) oil on the head of a person so that they receive a blessing, or as a sign of their special position.

Also: one who has received blessing or supernatural power from God.  In the Bible, the Old Testament supernatural anointing came with anointing of oil, and was relevant mainly to kings.  In other places in the Bible and the New Testament, "anointing of the Holy Spirit" comes to various believers.